From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PanicOS <panicos@localhost>
Date: Tue, 05 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] meson: disable wayland 1.22 symbol detection for PortMaster compat

PortMaster's westonwrap injects its own older libwayland-client.so.0 into
LD_LIBRARY_PATH ahead of /lib64.  That older wayland predates two functions
added in wayland 1.22:

  wl_display_dispatch_queue_timeout
  wl_display_create_queue_with_name

When Mesa is built against a system wayland >= 1.22, meson detects both
functions and sets HAVE_WL_DISPATCH_QUEUE_TIMEOUT / HAVE_WL_CREATE_QUEUE_WITH_NAME.
This disables Mesa's own fallback implementations in loader_wayland_helper.c
and causes libEGL.so to import the symbols as UNDEFINED from libwayland-client.so.0
at runtime.  PortMaster's dlopen of libEGL.so.1 then fails:

  undefined symbol: wl_display_dispatch_queue_timeout
  undefined symbol: wl_display_create_queue_with_name

Fix by removing both cc.has_function() probes so the symbols are never
detected.  Mesa's internal fallbacks in loader_wayland_helper.c are
compiled in unconditionally:

  wl_display_dispatch_queue_timeout  -> ppoll-based implementation
  wl_display_create_queue_with_name  -> wraps wl_display_create_queue (name ignored)

libEGL.so no longer has undefined imports for either symbol.
---
 meson.build | 12 ------------
 1 file changed, 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/meson.build b/meson.build
--- a/meson.build
+++ b/meson.build
@@ -2093,18 +2093,6 @@
     dep_wayland_egl_headers = dep_wayland_egl.partial_dependency(compile_args : true)
   endif
   pre_args += '-DWL_HIDE_DEPRECATED'
-  if cc.has_function(
-      'wl_display_dispatch_queue_timeout',
-      prefix : '#include <wayland-client.h>',
-      dependencies: dep_wayland_client)
-    pre_args += ['-DHAVE_WL_DISPATCH_QUEUE_TIMEOUT']
-  endif
-  if cc.has_function(
-      'wl_display_create_queue_with_name',
-      prefix : '#include <wayland-client.h>',
-      dependencies: dep_wayland_client)
-    pre_args += ['-DHAVE_WL_CREATE_QUEUE_WITH_NAME']
-  endif
   # This can be renamed just `wayland` when we require at least 1.8
   mod_wl = import('unstable-wayland')
 endif
